Here are the top 5 must-know Lambda interview topics:

1. Cold Start

What:
  First invocation → AWS spins up container → slow
  Subsequent calls → container warm → fast

Why it happens:
  Lambda scales to zero when not in use
  New container needed on first call

How to fix:
  Provisioned concurrency → pre-warm containers
  Ping every 5 mins → keep warm
  Smaller package size → faster startup
  Python/Node → faster than Java

2. Lambda vs EC2

Lambda:
  ✅ no server management
  ✅ scales to zero
  ✅ pay per execution
  ❌ max 15 min
  ❌ stateless
  ❌ cold start

EC2:
  ✅ long running
  ✅ stateful
  ✅ full control
  ❌ pay even idle
  ❌ manage yourself

3. Triggers

S3          → file uploaded
API Gateway → HTTP request
CloudWatch  → scheduled cron
SQS         → queue message
SNS         → notification
DynamoDB    → table change
Cognito     → user signup

4. Concurrency

What:
  Number of Lambda instances
  running at same time

Types:
  Reserved    → guarantee X for one function
  Provisioned → pre-warmed, no cold start

Default limit:
  1000 per region
  Can request increase from AWS

Throttle:
  Limit exceeded → Lambda throttled
  Fix → SQS queue in front of Lambda

5. VPC Lambda

When to use:
  Lambda needs RDS access ✅
  Lambda needs private resources ✅

How:
  Configure VPC + private subnet + SG
  Lambda gets private IP

Problem:
  Cold start increases (ENI creation)
  Needs NAT Gateway for internet access

Best practice:
  Only put Lambda in VPC when necessary
  Not needed for S3, DynamoDB (use VPC endpoints)
